00:26:03,833 --> 00:26:05,200
-COME ON, RODGE.

474
00:26:05,233 --> 00:26:07,467
YOU DO FINE.

475
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:10,433
-WELL, YOU KNOW, FINE...

476
00:26:10,467 --> 00:26:12,800
ISN'T FINE ANYMORE.

477
00:26:12,833 --> 00:26:14,733
IT USED TO BE.

478
00:26:14,767 --> 00:26:17,767
IT'S A DIFFERENT WORLD.

479
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:20,367
I'M LIKE EVERYBODY ELSE.
YOU KNOW, I WANT LUXURY.

480
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:21,800
I'D LIKE TO HAVE A SPORTS CAR.

481
00:26:21,833 --> 00:26:24,667
YOU KNOW,
I'D JUST LIKE TO OWN ONE ONCE.

482
00:26:24,700 --> 00:26:28,600
-WELL, YOU KNOW, I'M, UH --
I'M NOT GONNA LIE TO YOU, RODGE.

483
00:26:28,633 --> 00:26:30,667
IT'S A GREAT FEELING, YOU KNOW?

484
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:32,533
-YEAH.
-COME ON.

485
00:26:32,567 --> 00:26:35,800
I DON'T WANT TO -- I DON'T
WANT TO RUB SALT IN YOUR WOUNDS.

486
00:26:35,833 --> 00:26:38,467
IT'S, UH --
YOU GOT A NICE HOUSE, YOU KNOW?

487
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:41,100
YOU GOT SWEET KIDS,
A FUCKING HOT-ASS WIFE.

488
00:26:41,133 --> 00:26:45,800
YOU KNOW, IF YOU ASK ME,
YOU'RE A LUCKY GUY.

489
00:26:45,833 --> 00:26:48,367
-YOU THINK SO?

490
00:26:51,067 --> 00:26:53,100
-I, UH --

491
00:26:53,133 --> 00:26:57,667
I GOT A LITTLE TIP FOR YOU.

492
00:26:57,700 --> 00:27:01,667
ROGER, YOU EVER, UH...

493
00:27:01,700 --> 00:27:07,200
YOU EVER CONSIDER INVESTING
IN, UH, COPPER CANYON ESTATES?

494
00:27:07,233 --> 00:27:10,467
-OH [CHUCKLES] I CAN'T INVEST.

495
00:27:10,500 --> 00:27:13,300
I COULD BARELY SCRAPE UP

496
00:27:13,333 --> 00:27:15,433
THE MEMBERSHIP FEE
FOR THE CLUB THIS YEAR.

497
00:27:15,467 --> 00:27:17,300
-WELL, TELL YOUR WIFE
TO GET A JOB.

498
00:27:17,333 --> 00:27:18,800
-I DID.

499
00:27:18,833 --> 00:27:20,167
-[ CHUCKLES ]

500
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:22,100
GOOD LORD, MAN.
I WAS JOKING.

501
00:27:22,133 --> 00:27:24,567
-[ LAUGHS ]

502
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:28,200
-ALL RIGHT, LISTEN.

503
00:27:28,233 --> 00:27:32,633
IF YOU CAN GET YOUR HANDS
ON $100,000,

504
00:27:32,667 --> 00:27:36,300
I CAN MAKE YOU A RICH MAN.

505
00:27:38,667 --> 00:27:40,067
I GOT TO RUN.

506
00:27:40,100 --> 00:27:43,467
SO, WE'LL, UH,
SEE YOU HERE ON SATURDAY

507
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:45,533
FOR THE, UH, SKINS GAME?

508
00:27:45,567 --> 00:27:46,600
-YEAH.

509
00:27:46,633 --> 00:27:48,533
-OKAY.

510
00:27:58,200 --> 00:28:00,267
-WHAT'S THAT?

511
00:28:03,167 --> 00:28:04,433
OH.

512
00:28:04,467 --> 00:28:06,200
CAN I BORROW IT
WHEN YOU'RE DONE, KID?

513
00:28:06,233 --> 00:28:08,100
-SURE.

514
00:28:08,133 --> 00:28:09,333
-THANKS.

515
00:28:09,367 --> 00:28:11,467
-GO, GIRLS!
[ BANGS ]

516
00:28:11,500 --> 00:28:13,200
LUNCHTIME'S OVER!

517
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:20,500
-HEY, HENRY,
DON'T USE THE 3/4 INCH.

518
00:28:20,533 --> 00:28:22,633
I TOLD YOU A THOUSAND TIMES --
USE THE 1/4 INCH.

519
00:28:22,667 --> 00:28:24,600
-WELL, THAT'S TOO THIN.
IT'S NOT SAFE.

520
00:28:24,633 --> 00:28:26,400
-HEY, LOOK, KID.

521
00:28:26,433 --> 00:28:30,133
STOP QUESTIONING ME, OKAY?
JUST DO WHAT I SAY, ALL RIGHT?

522
00:28:35,233 --> 00:28:37,700
-I LIKE THIS.

523
00:28:37,733 --> 00:28:41,300
-YEAH, IT'S PRETTY.

524
00:28:41,333 --> 00:28:44,033
[ BELL RINGS ]

525
00:28:44,067 --> 00:28:45,600
-[ SIGHS ]
I LOVE JEWELRY.

526
00:28:45,633 --> 00:28:47,267
OH, MY GOD!
OH, MY GOD!

527
00:28:47,300 --> 00:28:49,800
I JUST SAW A PICTURE
OF MADONNA WEARING THIS.

528
00:28:49,833 --> 00:28:51,600
OH, MY GOD.
THAT'S SO CUTE.

529
00:28:51,633 --> 00:28:53,767
I HAVE TO HAVE IT.
HOW MUCH IS THIS?

530
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:55,133
-IT'S $325.

531
00:28:55,167 --> 00:28:56,667
-OKAY, HOW MANY
DO YOU HAVE LEFT?

532
00:28:56,700 --> 00:28:58,367
-WELL,
IT'S A J.D. ELLIE ORIGINAL,

533
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:00,467
SO ONLY 200 ARE MADE,
BUT THIS IS THE LAST ONE.

534
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:03,033
-OKAY, CAN I --
CAN I PUT A HOLD ON IT?

535
00:29:03,067 --> 00:29:06,100
-I CAN HOLD IT FOR YOU
IF YOU GIVE ME A 20% DEPOSIT.

536
00:29:06,133 --> 00:29:07,567
-OKAY, UM...

537
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:09,267
[ SIGHS ]

538
00:29:09,300 --> 00:29:10,367
SHIT.

539
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:12,700
I ONLY HAVE $40.

540
00:29:12,733 --> 00:29:16,067
-DO YOU REALLY NEED IT?

541
00:29:16,100 --> 00:29:20,233
-NO, BUT I WANT IT.

542
00:29:20,267 --> 00:29:22,300
[ GIGGLES ]

543
00:29:22,333 --> 00:29:24,233
THANK YOU.

544
00:29:24,267 --> 00:29:27,033
OKAY. UM, MY NAME IS SUZI.
YOU CAN PUT IT UNDER THAT.

545
00:29:27,067 --> 00:29:28,067
-OKAY.

546
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:29,567
-YAY.

547
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:33,633
-JESUS.

548
00:29:33,667 --> 00:29:35,700
-CLUB FACE IS WIDE OPEN, ROGER.

549
00:29:35,733 --> 00:29:38,800
ROOKIE MOVE.
YOU'RE BETTER THAN THAT.

550
00:29:38,833 --> 00:29:42,600
-YEAH. THAT'S WHAT IT'S LIKE
LATELY, YOU KNOW?

551
00:29:42,633 --> 00:29:45,667
I'M JUST A BUTTON-DOWN
BENCH WARMER.

552
00:29:45,700 --> 00:29:48,300
-WELL, YOU SEEM TO BE DOING
SOMETHING RIGHT.

553
00:29:48,333 --> 00:29:50,333
AND CYNTHIA'S TURNED INTO,

554
00:29:50,367 --> 00:29:53,733
UH, QUITE THE YOUNG LADY
THE LAST FEW YEARS.

555
00:29:53,767 --> 00:29:55,300
-YEAH. IT'S TRUE.

556
00:29:55,333 --> 00:29:57,367
MAKES UP FOR HENRY.

557
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:59,367
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

558
00:30:02,500 --> 00:30:04,667
HEY, PAT.

559
00:30:04,700 --> 00:30:05,700
-HEY.

560
00:30:05,733 --> 00:30:08,033
-YOU GONNA -- YOU GONNA GOLF?

561
00:30:08,067 --> 00:30:09,400
-YEAH.

562
00:30:09,433 --> 00:30:12,633
I'VE BEEN LOOKING TO EXPAND
MY SOCIAL HOBBIES

563
00:30:12,667 --> 00:30:16,500
TO INCLUDE A SPORT
WHERE ONE CAN CONVERSATE

564
00:30:16,533 --> 00:30:18,367
WITH ONE'S OPPONENT.

565
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:20,733
-ALL RIGHT.
GOOD FOR YOU.

566
00:30:20,767 --> 00:30:24,067
-CARE TO JOIN ME
FOR A QUICK NINE?

567
00:30:24,100 --> 00:30:26,767
-YEAH, OKAY.
WHY THE HELL NOT?

568
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:30,167
-HOW ABOUT YOU?
YOU WANT A QUICKIE?

569
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:32,600
-[ CHUCKLES ]
I'LL PASS.

570
00:30:35,733 --> 00:30:38,300
-CAN I DRIVE?
-SURE.

571
00:30:38,333 --> 00:30:41,133
-REALLY?
-BE MY GUEST.

572
00:30:48,333 --> 00:30:51,233
CAN I ASK YOU SOMETHING?

573
00:30:51,267 --> 00:30:52,333
-SURE.

574
00:30:52,367 --> 00:30:55,233
-PROMISE YOU WON'T LAUGH?

575
00:30:55,267 --> 00:30:57,567
-YEAH.

576
00:30:57,600 --> 00:31:01,733
-I'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT MY FUTURE.

577
00:31:01,767 --> 00:31:04,333
-IN WHAT REGARDS, PAT?

578
00:31:04,367 --> 00:31:06,700
-WELL, I GOT SOME MONEY
SAVED UP,

579
00:31:06,733 --> 00:31:08,433
AND I WANT TO INVEST IT.

580
00:31:08,467 --> 00:31:11,200
-WELL, THAT WOULD BE SMART, PAT.

581
00:31:11,233 --> 00:31:16,167
-YEAH, I WAS WONDERING IF YOU
COULD HELP ME OUT, ACTUALLY.

582
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:17,667
-I'D BE GLAD TO.

583
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:21,700
HOW MUCH ARE WE TALKING?

584
00:31:21,733 --> 00:31:26,200
-YOU KNOW, I DON'T KNOW.
I SHOULD LOOK INTO THAT.

585
00:31:26,233 --> 00:31:28,033
-YOU SHOULD, YEAH.

586
00:31:29,367 --> 00:31:32,167
-IT JUST BUGS ME
THAT EVERYONE'S ALWAYS --

587
00:31:32,200 --> 00:31:35,133
EVERYONE'S GETTING IN ON IT
BUT ME, YOU KNOW?

588
00:31:35,167 --> 00:31:39,100
TALKING ABOUT THEIR INVESTMENTS,
HOW MUCH MONEY THEY'RE MAKING.

589
00:31:39,133 --> 00:31:42,200
I DON'T WANT TO TEACH TENNIS
ANYMORE.

590
00:31:42,233 --> 00:31:45,233
-NONE OF US DO, PAT.
NONE OF US DO.

591
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:53,200
-WOW.

592
00:31:53,233 --> 00:31:55,267
SHIT.

593
00:31:55,300 --> 00:31:57,433
STRAIGHT AND TRUE.

594
00:31:57,467 --> 00:32:00,200
WHERE'D THAT COME FROM?

595
00:32:00,233 --> 00:32:01,600
NICE SHOT.

596
00:32:03,300 --> 00:32:06,733
-I WANT US TO GET INVOLVED
WITH COPPER CANYON ESTATES.

597
00:32:06,767 --> 00:32:09,767
I NEED YOU TO NETWORK
WITH SOME OF THE PEOPLE

598
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:12,533
THAT ARE GONNA BE
AT THE PARTY TONIGHT.

599
00:32:12,567 --> 00:32:16,433
-AND WHERE AM I SUPPOSED TO GET
AHOLD OF THAT KIND OF CASH?

600
00:32:16,467 --> 00:32:19,733
WHAT SHOULD WE DO --
MARKET CYNTHIA'S COLLEGE FUND?

601
00:32:19,767 --> 00:32:21,100
-THAT'S A THOUGHT.

602
00:32:21,133 --> 00:32:22,600
-THAT'S SICK.

603
00:32:22,633 --> 00:32:25,333
SERIOUSLY, HOW AM I GONNA GET
THAT KIND OF MONEY?

604
00:32:25,367 --> 00:32:27,100
I MEAN, CAN'T GET A LOAN.

605
00:32:27,133 --> 00:32:29,500
IT'S AGAINST POLICY.
YOU KNOW THAT.

606
00:32:29,533 --> 00:32:31,333
-YOU WORK AT A BANK, ROGER.

607
00:32:31,367 --> 00:32:34,100
THERE ARE OTHER WAYS
TO BORROW MONEY.

608
00:32:37,367 --> 00:32:40,567
-I MISS THE FIREFLIES.

609
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:43,333
-THEY'LL BE BACK.

610
00:32:43,367 --> 00:32:46,733
-I KNOW,
BUT I WISH THEY WERE HERE NOW.

611
00:32:49,367 --> 00:32:53,500
-YOU KNOW, MALE FIREFLIES
ARE BORN WITH THIS CHEMICAL

612
00:32:53,533 --> 00:32:57,133
THAT MAKES THEM TASTE BAD
TO THE PREDATORS,

613
00:32:57,167 --> 00:33:00,767
AND THE FEMALES,
WELL, THEY'RE BORN WITHOUT IT.

614
00:33:00,800 --> 00:33:05,200
SO THE ONLY WAY THEY CAN GET
THE DEFENSE MECHANISM IS,

615
00:33:05,233 --> 00:33:08,467
YOU KNOW,
SOMETIMES THEY EAT THE MALES.

616
00:33:08,500 --> 00:33:09,733
-KIDS.

617
00:33:09,767 --> 00:33:12,733
-SPEAK OF THE DEVIL.

618
00:33:12,767 --> 00:33:14,500
-YOUR FATHER AND I
ARE GOING OUT.

619
00:33:14,533 --> 00:33:16,267
HENRY,
KEEP AN EYE ON YOUR SISTER.

620
00:33:16,300 --> 00:33:17,633
-I DON'T NEED A BABYSITTER.

621
00:33:17,667 --> 00:33:20,033
-FINE, THEN WATCH YOUR BROTHER.

622
00:33:20,067 --> 00:33:22,800
-IS IT OKAY IF SUZI SLEEPS OVER?
-YES.

623
00:33:22,833 --> 00:33:26,233
-I'M GOING OUT TO GET DRUNK
AND RACE GOLF CARTS.

624
00:33:26,267 --> 00:33:29,467
-OKAY, DEAR.
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

625
00:33:31,833 --> 00:33:35,133
-SO JUST ONE DRINK
AND WE'RE OUT OF HERE, OKAY?

626
00:33:35,167 --> 00:33:37,300
-NO. NO.
WE'RE NOT OUT OF HERE.

627
00:33:37,333 --> 00:33:39,600
WHY DIDN'T YOU WEAR
A SPORT COAT?

628
00:33:39,633 --> 00:33:41,367
[ SIGHS ]

629
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:44,033
JUST -- LOOK, PRETEND TO HAVE
A GOOD TIME, WOULD YOU?

630
00:33:44,067 --> 00:33:46,667
-BETTER YET,
JUST PRETEND YOU'RE NOT YOU.

631
00:33:46,700 --> 00:33:47,700
SMILE.

632
00:33:47,733 --> 00:33:49,533
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

633
00:33:49,567 --> 00:33:50,633
HELLO.

634
00:33:50,667 --> 00:33:53,500
-WELCOME, WELCOME
TO OUR NEW HOME.

635
00:33:53,533 --> 00:33:55,700
-THERE THEY ARE.
-OH, MY.

636
00:33:55,733 --> 00:33:58,633
-YOU LOOK GORGEOUS.
-OH, THANK YOU.

637
00:33:58,667 --> 00:34:00,133
-ROGER.
-HI.

638
00:34:00,167 --> 00:34:02,600
-HAVE A DRINK.
I'VE HAD THREE.

639
00:34:02,633 --> 00:34:04,033
-[ CHUCKLES ]

640
00:34:04,067 --> 00:34:06,633
-GEORGIE, WELCOME.
-OH, THANK YOU.

641
00:34:06,667 --> 00:34:10,167
OH, MY GOODNESS.
THE PLACE IS SO BEAUTIFUL.

642
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:11,400
MUST'VE COST A FORTUNE.

643
00:34:11,433 --> 00:34:13,233
-YEAH, BUT, YOU KNOW,
IT WAS WORTH IT.

644
00:34:13,267 --> 00:34:14,467
IT'S OUR HOUSE.

645
00:34:14,500 --> 00:34:16,167
-SHE SPENT WEEKS
FINDING THE RIGHT PIECES.

646
00:34:16,200 --> 00:34:18,500
-AREN'T YOU WORRIED
THAT IT MIGHT GO OUT OF STYLE?

647
00:34:18,533 --> 00:34:21,167
-YEAH, OF COURSE, BUT, YOU KNOW,
I'LL JUST REDECORATE.

648
00:34:21,200 --> 00:34:23,667
IT SHOULD STAY IN STYLE
FOR AT LEAST TWO TO FIVE YEARS.

649
00:34:23,700 --> 00:34:25,233
-TELL THEM ABOUT YOUR NEW TOY.

650
00:34:25,267 --> 00:34:28,433
-OH. I'M GONNA INSTALL
A TANNING BED COME FALL.

651
00:34:28,467 --> 00:34:29,467
-OOH.

652
00:34:29,500 --> 00:34:31,133
-I CAN'T WAIT.
-PERFECT.

653
00:34:31,167 --> 00:34:34,333
NOW I'LL HAVE A TAN
BEFORE I GO TO SAINT CROIX.

654
00:34:34,367 --> 00:34:37,233
-OH, UH, ROGER AND I
WERE THINKING ABOUT

655
00:34:37,267 --> 00:34:38,667
GOING TO SAINT CROIX.

656
00:34:38,700 --> 00:34:41,767
[ BUBBLING ]

657
00:34:42,800 --> 00:34:45,733
-HERE IT IS...

658
00:34:45,767 --> 00:34:48,100
[ SIGHS ]

659
00:34:48,133 --> 00:34:51,667
...A NEW WATERING SYSTEM --

660
00:34:51,700 --> 00:34:58,200
UTILIZES PRESSURIZED TUBING,
MICROSCOPIC PIN PRICKS.

661
00:34:58,233 --> 00:35:04,367
IT'S PRETTY GENIUS, ACTUALLY.

662
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:07,800
-WHAT QUALIFIES SOMEONE
TO BE A GENIUS?

663
00:35:07,833 --> 00:35:12,500
-WELL, TECHNICALLY, I THINK
IT'S AN IQ OF 140 OR HIGHER.

664
00:35:12,533 --> 00:35:15,767
BUT THERE ARE VARIOUS KINDS
OF GENIUS.

665
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:19,167
MINE JUST HAPPENS TO BE
HORTICULTURE.

666
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:21,367
-BUT YOU'RE A GROUNDS KEEPER.

667
00:35:23,333 --> 00:35:27,067
HORTICULTURE
IS THE SCIENCE AND ART

668
00:35:27,100 --> 00:35:33,133
OF GROWING FRUITS, VEGETABLES,
FLOWERS, AND ORNAMENTAL PLANTS.

669
00:35:40,400 --> 00:35:42,233
-SO HOW DO WE GET INVOLVED
IN PHASE TWO?

670
00:35:42,267 --> 00:35:44,400
-WELL, IF YOU TURN TO PAGE THREE
OF THE PERSPECTIVES,

671
00:35:44,433 --> 00:35:45,633
IT WILL EXPLAIN ALL OF IT.

672
00:35:45,667 --> 00:35:48,033
AND YOU'LL NOTICE
THAT THE, UH -- THE AREA

673
00:35:48,067 --> 00:35:49,767
WHERE THE INDIAN
CEREMONIAL GROUND

674
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:51,600
SUPPOSEDLY USED TO BE...
-RIGHT.

675
00:35:51,633 --> 00:35:53,300
-...IS 70% COMPLETE.

676
00:35:53,333 --> 00:35:55,467
AND WITH YOUR INVESTMENT,
WE'LL ACQUIRE THE TREE FARM

677
00:35:55,500 --> 00:35:57,533
THAT BORDERS ON THE SOUTH SIDE.
-OKAY.

678
00:35:57,567 --> 00:35:59,800
-I MEAN, WHO THE HELL
NEEDS CHRISTMAS TREES,

679
00:35:59,833 --> 00:36:01,200
FOR CHRIST'S SAKE,

680
00:36:01,233 --> 00:36:02,800
WHEN YOU'RE LOOKING
AT 300% RETURNS?

681
00:36:02,833 --> 00:36:04,133
[ LAUGHTER ]

682
00:36:04,167 --> 00:36:06,033
-[ CHUCKLES ]

683
00:36:06,067 --> 00:36:07,567
-LENT.
-HEY.

684
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:10,067
-YOU KNOW WHAT, GUYS?
UH, I'LL BE BACK IN A SECOND.

685
00:36:10,100 --> 00:36:12,333
ROGER, LET'S, UH,
LET'S TAKE A WALK.

686
00:36:12,367 --> 00:36:13,667
-OKAY.

687
00:36:13,700 --> 00:36:15,633
-[ SNORTS ]

688
00:36:15,667 --> 00:36:18,667
[ SIGHS ]

689
00:36:18,700 --> 00:36:20,300
[ SIGHS ]

690
00:36:20,333 --> 00:36:22,033
[ SNIFFS ]

691
00:36:22,067 --> 00:36:23,433
[ SIGHS ]

692
00:36:23,467 --> 00:36:25,167
[ SNIFFS ]

693
00:36:25,200 --> 00:36:26,233
RODGE?

694
00:36:26,267 --> 00:36:28,500
-NOPE. THANK YOU.
I'LL PASS.

695
00:36:28,533 --> 00:36:30,567
-ARE YOU SURE?
-YEP.

696
00:36:30,600 --> 00:36:33,600
-IT'S PURE PINK PERUVIAN FLAKE,
MAN -- THE BEST.

697
00:36:33,633 --> 00:36:36,600
NONE OF THAT COLOMBIAN CRAP.

698
00:36:36,633 --> 00:36:40,467
-I HAVEN'T, YOU KNOW,
SINCE COLLEGE.

699
00:36:40,500 --> 00:36:42,333
-[ CHUCKLES ]

700
00:36:44,333 --> 00:36:47,633
-WOW. THAT'S A LOT, MAN.

701
00:36:47,667 --> 00:36:50,067
WHERE'D YOU GET THAT?
IN THE CITY?

702
00:36:50,100 --> 00:36:51,767
-[ SCOFFS ]
GOD, NO.

703
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:56,133
COPPER CANYON COUNTRY CLUB --
OUR INFAMOUS TENNIS PRO.

704
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,567
WHAT?

705
00:37:00,600 --> 00:37:02,133
[ CHUCKLES ]
