1401
01:14:34,833 --> 01:14:36,100
-YOU WHAT?!

1402
01:14:36,133 --> 01:14:37,600
-WELL, I STOLE IT.

1403
01:14:37,633 --> 01:14:38,667
-YOU --

1404
01:14:38,700 --> 01:14:41,033
BUT HOW COULD THAT BE?

1405
01:14:41,067 --> 01:14:44,800
YOU'RE --
YOU'RE A NORMAL BUSINESS GUY.

1406
01:14:44,833 --> 01:14:49,267
-WELL, YEAH,
NORMAL PEOPLE DO BAD THINGS.

1407
01:14:49,300 --> 01:14:51,533
-WHAT THE FUCK DOES THAT MEAN?!

1408
01:14:51,567 --> 01:14:53,233
-WELL, IT MEANS
THAT YOUR MONEY IS GONE.

1409
01:14:53,267 --> 01:14:57,467
-GONE? FOR HOW LONG?

1410
01:14:57,500 --> 01:14:58,500
-FOREVER.

1411
01:14:58,533 --> 01:14:59,533
-FUCK!

1412
01:14:59,567 --> 01:15:01,800
JESUS FUCKING CHRIST!

1413
01:15:01,833 --> 01:15:03,500
-LOOK, YOU KNOW, THAT'S --

1414
01:15:03,533 --> 01:15:05,100
-OH, FUCK!
-PAT --

1415
01:15:05,133 --> 01:15:07,367
PAT, Y-YOU KNOW,
THIS IS WHAT HAPPENS, YOU KNOW?

1416
01:15:07,400 --> 01:15:09,800
YOU RUN THIS KIND OF RISK
WHEN YOU DO STUFF LIKE THAT.

1417
01:15:09,833 --> 01:15:12,067
YOU TAKE A RISK.

1418
01:15:12,100 --> 01:15:13,767
-WELL, YOU'RE A --
LOOK AT YOU.

1419
01:15:13,800 --> 01:15:15,733
YOU'RE A FATHER.
YOU'RE A FATHER.

1420
01:15:15,767 --> 01:15:18,300
YOU'RE A REGULAR FATHER.
DON'T YOU FEEL BAD?

1421
01:15:18,333 --> 01:15:21,267
-I DO. Y-YEAH.
-YOU DO?

1422
01:15:21,300 --> 01:15:25,567
YOU DON'T LOOK LIKE IT.
YOU DON'T LOOK LIKE YOU DO.

1423
01:15:25,600 --> 01:15:28,433
-WELL, IT'S NOT LIKE THE MONEY
WAS LEGITIMATE ANYWAY, RIGHT?

1424
01:15:28,467 --> 01:15:30,100
[ SCOFFS ]

1425
01:15:30,133 --> 01:15:31,400
R-RIGHT?

1426
01:15:31,433 --> 01:15:33,433
HEY, HEY, HEY.

1427
01:15:33,467 --> 01:15:36,500
I-I JUST WANT WHAT
EVERYBODY ELSE DOES, YOU KNOW?

1428
01:15:36,533 --> 01:15:39,600
I JUST WANTED AN --
A LITTLE EXTRA, YOU KNOW, PAT?

1429
01:15:39,633 --> 01:15:42,067
LIKE, YOU KNOW, SOMETHING...

1430
01:15:42,100 --> 01:15:43,667
I JUST WANTED TO...

1431
01:15:43,700 --> 01:15:47,600
YOU KNOW WHAT IT IS?
THEY DON'T LET YOU WIN.

1432
01:15:47,633 --> 01:15:49,533
T-THEY DON'T LET YOU.

1433
01:15:49,567 --> 01:15:53,500
AND...

1434
01:15:53,533 --> 01:15:57,200
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING ELSE
TO SAY BUT THAT.

1435
01:15:59,133 --> 01:16:02,567
-IT'S --

1436
01:16:02,600 --> 01:16:04,233
IT'S NOT COOL.

1437
01:16:04,267 --> 01:16:08,600
DOESN'T MAKE IT COOL.
DOESN'T MAKE IT COOL.

1438
01:16:14,067 --> 01:16:16,600
IT'S NOT COOL, YOU KNOW.
IT'S STILL NOT COOL.

1439
01:16:16,633 --> 01:16:18,133
IT'S NOT FUCKING COOL.

1440
01:16:23,167 --> 01:16:25,733
-I GOT A PROMOTION AT THE BANK.

1441
01:16:25,767 --> 01:16:29,433
YOU KNOW, LIKE, MAYBE,
DOWN T-THE ROAD,

1442
01:16:29,467 --> 01:16:32,233
I CAN FIX THIS THING, YOU KNOW?

1443
01:16:32,267 --> 01:16:35,667
GET SOME OF THAT MONEY BACK,
YOU KNOW?

1444
01:16:35,700 --> 01:16:37,400
MAYBE MOST OF IT.

1445
01:16:37,433 --> 01:16:40,633
GET YOU, LIKE,
SOME STOCK OPTIONS,

1446
01:16:40,667 --> 01:16:42,300
MAYBE AN I.P.O.

1447
01:16:49,100 --> 01:16:52,267
-I.P.O.? YOU'D DO THAT?

1448
01:16:52,300 --> 01:16:54,067
-I'LL TRY.

1449
01:16:54,100 --> 01:16:58,133
-AN I.P.O.? LIKE --
-YEAH.

1450
01:16:58,167 --> 01:17:02,367
-SOME STOCK OPTIONS?
-YEAH.

1451
01:17:10,400 --> 01:17:14,133
-THAT MIGHT BE COOL.
THAT MIGHT BE COOL.

1452
01:17:19,100 --> 01:17:22,133
[ MEAN CREEK'S "IT'S GOOD
TO BE BACK AGAIN" PLAYS ]

1453
01:17:22,167 --> 01:17:23,800
-I DO HAVE AN IDEA, THOUGH,

1454
01:17:23,833 --> 01:17:27,200
THAT WOULD BE A GOOD THING
FOR THE BOTH OF US.

1455
01:17:32,367 --> 01:17:34,200
-YEAH!

1456
01:17:34,233 --> 01:17:38,567
-* I DON'T MIND GOING DOWN
INTO THE DIRT UNDERGROUND *

1457
01:17:38,600 --> 01:17:43,700
* AS LONG AS I CAN HEAR THE SONG
YOU'VE BEEN SINGIN' ALL ALONG *

1458
01:17:43,733 --> 01:17:45,500
* HEY, HEY, LOOK AT YOU

1459
01:17:45,533 --> 01:17:48,067
* SPEAKIN' YOUR MIND,
SINGIN' THE TRUTH *

1460
01:17:48,100 --> 01:17:50,333
* OH, MY, WHERE HAVE I BEEN?

1461
01:17:50,367 --> 01:17:53,267
* LORD, IT'S GOOD
TO BE BACK AGAIN *

1462
01:18:02,100 --> 01:18:04,400
* WHERE DO I GO WHEN I DIE?

1463
01:18:04,433 --> 01:18:07,100
* WHY AM I HERE?
WHO AM I? *

1464
01:18:07,133 --> 01:18:09,267
* WHO ARE YOU TO SAY TO ME

1465
01:18:09,300 --> 01:18:11,333
* WHAT IS SACRED TO BELIEVE?

1466
01:18:11,367 --> 01:18:13,500
* HEY, HEY, GOD IS DEAD

1467
01:18:13,533 --> 01:18:15,800
* WAS HE ALWAYS
JUST IN MY HEAD? *

1468
01:18:15,833 --> 01:18:18,533
* OH, MY, WHERE HAVE I BEEN?

1469
01:18:18,567 --> 01:18:21,400
* LORD, IT'S GOOD
TO BE BACK AGAIN *

1470
01:18:37,367 --> 01:18:38,433
-HEY.

1471
01:18:38,467 --> 01:18:41,400
WHAT ARE YOU WRITING?

1472
01:18:41,433 --> 01:18:43,333
-MY JOURNAL.

1473
01:18:43,367 --> 01:18:47,100
-WHAT ARE YOU WRITING ABOUT?

1474
01:18:47,133 --> 01:18:48,400
-STUFF.

1475
01:18:48,433 --> 01:18:51,067
HOW'D YOU FIND ME?

1476
01:18:51,100 --> 01:18:52,600
-I FOLLOWED YOU.

1477
01:18:52,633 --> 01:18:54,600
-THAT'S A BAD HABIT.

1478
01:18:54,633 --> 01:18:56,167
-[ CHUCKLES ]

1479
01:18:56,200 --> 01:18:59,533
I-I KNOW,
BUT I WANTED TO SEE YOU.

1480
01:18:59,567 --> 01:19:02,167
-WHY?
WHAT DO YOU CARE?

1481
01:19:02,200 --> 01:19:05,100
-I MEAN,
SHOULDN'T YOU BE OUT PLAYING WAR

1482
01:19:05,133 --> 01:19:08,033
OR LOOKING FOR FROGS
OR WHATEVER BOYS DO?

1483
01:19:08,067 --> 01:19:11,133
-I DON'T KNOW.
I-I JUST WANTED TO HANG OUT.

1484
01:19:19,367 --> 01:19:22,133
-I GOT TO GO, JOSH.

1485
01:19:22,167 --> 01:19:23,700
-UM, OKAY.

1486
01:19:23,733 --> 01:19:28,800
UH, MAYBE WE COULD, UH,
GO SEE A MOVIE OR SOMETHING.

1487
01:19:28,833 --> 01:19:32,400
-LIKE ON A DATE?

1488
01:19:32,433 --> 01:19:35,533
-YEAH, I GUESS.

1489
01:19:35,567 --> 01:19:36,700
-UM...

1490
01:19:36,733 --> 01:19:41,467
-YEAH, L-LET ME TAKE YOU
ON A DATE.

1491
01:19:41,500 --> 01:19:44,667
-ARE YOU SURE?
-YEAH.

1492
01:19:44,700 --> 01:19:48,033
-OKAY. GOOD.

1493
01:19:48,067 --> 01:19:51,267
IT'S ABOUT TIME
YOU ASKED ME OUT.

1494
01:19:53,700 --> 01:19:57,733
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

1495
01:19:57,767 --> 01:20:00,800
-I DON'T KNOW.

1496
01:20:00,833 --> 01:20:03,067
I JUST GOT TO GO.

1497
01:20:05,133 --> 01:20:08,500
I'LL COME BACK AND SEE YOU.

1498
01:20:08,533 --> 01:20:10,200
I PROMISE.

1499
01:20:10,233 --> 01:20:15,033
-WHAT HAPPENED?

1500
01:20:15,067 --> 01:20:17,533
-UM...

1501
01:20:17,567 --> 01:20:22,067
WHEN YOU GET OLD -- OLDER,

1502
01:20:22,100 --> 01:20:27,700
YOU -- YOU DO THINGS THAT COULD
CAUSE OTHER PEOPLE PROBLEMS.

1503
01:20:27,733 --> 01:20:33,067
AND THEY CAN CAUSE YOURSELF
PROBLEMS, TOO.

1504
01:20:33,100 --> 01:20:36,133
AND YOU'RE AWARE OF THIS,

1505
01:20:36,167 --> 01:20:41,533
BUT YOU DO THEM ANYWAY
'CAUSE IT FEELS RIGHT.

1506
01:20:41,567 --> 01:20:45,267
-YOU'RE IN TROUBLE, AREN'T YOU?

1507
01:20:45,300 --> 01:20:48,067
-ONLY IF I GET CAUGHT.

1508
01:20:48,100 --> 01:20:49,100
HERE.

1509
01:20:49,133 --> 01:20:52,133
-I LOVE YOU, HENRY.

1510
01:21:04,833 --> 01:21:10,733
"THE EARTH IS RELEVANT
IN OUR CONTAINED PERSPECTIVE."

1511
01:21:14,367 --> 01:21:15,633
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

1512
01:21:15,667 --> 01:21:17,400
-[ SIGHS ]

1513
01:21:23,300 --> 01:21:26,267
I'M GONNA GIVE THIS TO YOU NOW.

1514
01:21:26,300 --> 01:21:30,700
LOOK, I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW
THAT'S LIKE --

1515
01:21:33,633 --> 01:21:36,533
THAT'S LIKE HALF THE MONEY
I GOT IN THE WORLD RIGHT NOW.

1516
01:21:36,567 --> 01:21:38,667
-WELL, YOU SHOULD'VE
THOUGHT ABOUT THAT

1517
01:21:38,700 --> 01:21:40,267
BEFORE YOU GOT ME PREGNANT.

1518
01:21:43,233 --> 01:21:47,600
OH, NO. I'M GOOD.
I HAVE A RIDE HOME.

1519
01:21:47,633 --> 01:21:49,267
BYE.

1520
01:21:53,233 --> 01:21:55,133
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

1521
01:21:55,167 --> 01:21:59,067
[ CLOUD NOTHINGS'
"DIDN'T YOU" PLAYS ]

1522
01:22:41,100 --> 01:22:43,400
-IN LOCAL NEWS THIS MORNING,
POLICE ARE SEEKING A SUSPECT

1523
01:22:43,433 --> 01:22:45,067
IN THE APPARENT ARSON ATTACK

1524
01:22:45,100 --> 01:22:47,300
OF THE COPPER CANYON ESTATES
DEVELOPMENT

1525
01:22:47,333 --> 01:22:49,133
JUST SOUTH OF ROUTE 16.

1526
01:22:49,167 --> 01:22:51,367
AN UNIDENTIFIED BODY
WAS RECOVERED FROM THE RUBBLE,

1527
01:22:51,400 --> 01:22:54,233
BUT POLICE AREN'T RELEASING
ANY OTHER INFORMATION.

1528
01:22:54,267 --> 01:22:57,133
CONSTRUCTION OF THE LUXURY
HOMES WAS RECENTLY HALTED

1529
01:22:57,167 --> 01:22:59,500
AMIDST ALLEGATIONS
OF FINANCIAL IMPROPRIETY

1530
01:22:59,533 --> 01:23:01,200
INVOLVING
BOTH THE LEAD CONTRACTOR

1531
01:23:01,233 --> 01:23:03,633
AND THE DEVELOPER,
THE LINDSEY GROUP.

1532
01:23:03,667 --> 01:23:07,800
-BEAUTIFUL DAY FOR PAT McKENNA!

1533
01:23:07,833 --> 01:23:14,600
McKENNA'S NOW TURNED
HIS PRODIGIOUS CAPABILITIES

1534
01:23:14,633 --> 01:23:15,800
INTO THE WORLD OF FINANCE.

1535
01:23:15,833 --> 01:23:18,033
-WHAT ARE YOU READING?

1536
01:23:18,067 --> 01:23:19,533
-"THE ART OF WAR."

1537
01:23:19,567 --> 01:23:20,567
-WOW.

1538
01:23:20,600 --> 01:23:22,533
-HENRY GAVE IT TO ME.

1539
01:23:22,567 --> 01:23:24,767
-COPPER CANYON BANK.

1540
01:23:24,800 --> 01:23:26,300
-SO, HOW LONG'S HE BEEN AT THIS?

1541
01:23:26,333 --> 01:23:28,100
-McKENNA'S NOW REFOCUSED.

1542
01:23:28,133 --> 01:23:30,100
-UH, COMING UP ON TWO HOURS.

1543
01:23:34,667 --> 01:23:37,767
-I CAME TO SAY GOODBYE
TO MY BOYS.

1544
01:23:37,800 --> 01:23:41,100
I'M GONNA TRY
THE BIG CITY AGAIN.

1545
01:23:42,500 --> 01:23:47,667
SO LET'S MAKE THIS QUICK, OKAY?

1546
01:23:47,700 --> 01:23:49,633
-ALL RIGHT.

1547
01:23:49,667 --> 01:23:53,133
-[ Chuckling ]
AWW.

1548
01:23:53,167 --> 01:23:56,267
TAKE CARE, ALL RIGHT?

1549
01:23:56,300 --> 01:23:59,567
LATER, GUYS.

1550
01:23:59,600 --> 01:24:02,133
-LATER.

1551
01:24:16,367 --> 01:24:19,267
-AH, THIS IS THE GOOD STUFF.

1552
01:24:19,300 --> 01:24:22,500
-CYNTHIA, HONEY,
HAVE YOU SEEN YOUR BROTHER?

1553
01:24:22,533 --> 01:24:26,233
THE POLICE WERE HERE
THIS MORNING LOOKING FOR HIM.

1554
01:24:26,267 --> 01:24:29,733
I'VE DRIVEN ALL AROUND TOWN,
AND I CAN'T FIND HIM.

1555
01:24:29,767 --> 01:24:31,600
DO YOU KNOW WHERE HE IS?

1556
01:24:31,633 --> 01:24:36,633
-UM, WELL, I DON'T THINK WE'LL
BE SEEING HIM FOR A LONG TIME.

1557
01:24:36,667 --> 01:24:37,700
-WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

1558
01:24:37,733 --> 01:24:39,167
-HE SPLIT TOWN

1559
01:24:39,200 --> 01:24:41,067
ON A TRIP, OR JOURNEY.

1560
01:24:41,100 --> 01:24:43,233
-CYNTHIA,
I HAVE TO KNOW WHERE HE IS!

1561
01:24:43,267 --> 01:24:45,100
-I DON'T KNOW WHERE HE IS,
AND EVEN IF I DID,

1562
01:24:45,133 --> 01:24:46,467
I PROBABLY WOULDN'T TELL YOU.

1563
01:24:46,500 --> 01:24:49,067
-YOU HAVEN'T BEEN RUNNING
THIS FAMILY LATELY,

1564
01:24:49,100 --> 01:24:51,367
SO I'VE LEARNED TO TOLERATE YOU.

1565
01:24:51,400 --> 01:24:53,567
[ BOTTLE CLINKS ]

1566
01:25:24,467 --> 01:25:26,500
-[ SIGHS ]

1567
01:25:38,167 --> 01:25:41,033
SOMETIMES,
WE MAKE DECISIONS IN LIFE

1568
01:25:41,067 --> 01:25:43,667
THAT HAVE FAR-REACHING
CONSEQUENCES

1569
01:25:43,700 --> 01:25:46,333
AND WE DON'T ALWAYS KNOW
WHAT THEY ARE

1570
01:25:46,367 --> 01:25:49,767
UNTIL IT'S TOO LATE.

1571
01:25:49,800 --> 01:25:53,167
-WHY IS ALL THIS SO HARD?

1572
01:25:53,200 --> 01:25:56,633
-I DON'T KNOW.

1573
01:25:56,667 --> 01:25:58,467
[ SIGHS ]

1574
01:25:58,500 --> 01:26:02,567
ADULTS CAN BE [SIGHS]
JUST AS RECKLESS AS CHILDREN,

1575
01:26:02,600 --> 01:26:06,167
EVEN THOUGH
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO KNOW BETTER.

1576
01:26:06,200 --> 01:26:08,333
-I DON'T WANT TO BE A GROWN-UP.

1577
01:26:08,367 --> 01:26:11,533
TOO MUCH RESPONSIBILITY
AND TOO MANY CHOICES.

1578
01:26:11,567 --> 01:26:13,167
IT SOUNDS LIKE SHIT.

1579
01:26:13,200 --> 01:26:16,800
-OH, IT'S NOT ALL SHIT, HONEY.

1580
01:26:16,833 --> 01:26:20,200
SOMETIMES, IT CAN BE FUN.

1581
01:26:20,233 --> 01:26:24,067
-I JUST WANT THINGS
TO BE NORMAL AGAIN.

1582
01:26:24,100 --> 01:26:26,533
-I THOUGHT I WANTED NORMAL.

1583
01:26:26,567 --> 01:26:32,267
AND THEN I REALIZED
THAT I DIDN'T.

1584
01:26:32,300 --> 01:26:36,600
I THINK THE BEST WE CAN HOPE FOR
IS TO COME HOME

1585
01:26:36,633 --> 01:26:38,367
AT THE END OF THE DAY

1586
01:26:38,400 --> 01:26:42,133
AND SEE THE PEOPLE
THAT WE CAN REALLY COUNT ON.

1587
01:26:44,333 --> 01:26:48,600
-"THE EARTH IS RELEVANT
IN OUR CONTAINED PERSPECTIVE."

1588
01:26:51,233 --> 01:26:53,267
-I THINK IT'S SWEET

1589
01:26:53,300 --> 01:26:57,300
THAT YOU'RE PROTECTING
YOUR BROTHER.

1590
01:27:08,433 --> 01:27:12,167
PUT THIS ONE HERE.

1591
01:27:12,200 --> 01:27:14,267
PERFECT.

1592
01:27:14,300 --> 01:27:15,567
AND THIS ONE.

1593
01:27:15,600 --> 01:27:16,800
SO PROUD.

1594
01:27:16,833 --> 01:27:19,767
"THIRD PLACE."
WELL, CLOSE ENOUGH.

1595
01:28:10,700 --> 01:28:14,800
-I GOT ANOTHER LETTER TODAY.

1596
01:28:14,833 --> 01:28:16,667
-FROM?

1597
01:28:16,700 --> 01:28:18,633
-TULSA.

1598
01:28:18,667 --> 01:28:20,367
-AND?

1599
01:28:20,400 --> 01:28:22,167
-AND THE USUAL,

1600
01:28:22,200 --> 01:28:25,067
BUT THE FEATHERS HE INCLUDED

1601
01:28:25,100 --> 01:28:29,167
WERE A LITTLE MORE COLORFUL
THIS TIME.

1602
01:28:29,200 --> 01:28:33,467
-I MISS HIM.
-ME, TOO.

1603
01:28:33,500 --> 01:28:36,600
-I-I WAS THINKING THAT WE'D, UM,

1604
01:28:36,633 --> 01:28:40,300
REPAINT THE WALLS
IN OUR BEDROOM,

1605
01:28:40,333 --> 01:28:44,067
MAYBE A FRESH COAT?
-OF THE HOUSE?

1606
01:28:44,100 --> 01:28:45,767
-YEAH. OUR HOME.

1607
01:28:52,600 --> 01:28:57,200
-YOU KNOW, THIS IS ALL
WE REALLY HAVE.

1608
01:28:57,233 --> 01:28:58,700
-I KNOW.

1609
01:28:58,733 --> 01:29:04,433
FROM NOW ON, I'LL AIM
FOR NON-LIFE-THREATENING SPORTS.

1610
01:29:04,467 --> 01:29:06,300
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

1611
01:29:06,333 --> 01:29:10,567
-I-I REALLY DO LIKE
THE NEW LOOK, THOUGH.

1612
01:29:10,600 --> 01:29:13,733
-WELL, GOT TO KEEP YOU GUESSING.

1613
01:29:13,767 --> 01:29:17,600
-YEAH.
MAYBE A LITTLE LESS TEQUILA.

1614
01:29:17,633 --> 01:29:20,133
-MAYBE.

1615
01:29:20,167 --> 01:29:22,033
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

1616
01:30:04,800 --> 01:30:08,633
[ MAMMALS'
"WIRES AND BUTTONS" PLAYS ]

1617
01:30:41,400 --> 01:30:44,133
* DON'T LET HER
TOUCH YOUR BACK *

1618
01:30:44,167 --> 01:30:47,567
* 'CAUSE I KNOW
I'M ON THE STREET *

1619
01:30:47,600 --> 01:30:51,167
* AND I KNOW OF
ALL THE THINGS *

1620
01:30:51,200 --> 01:30:54,600
* THAT YOU KNOW
THAT THEY CAN'T MEET *

